  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong>,<strong> </strong>reduce the heat to low and cook for a further 6-7 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1652259099210-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1652259099210-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1652259099210-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1652259099210-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1652259099210-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under the <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can then chop it roughly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1652259109293-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1652259109293-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1652259109293-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1652259109293-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1652259109293-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> soft cheese</strong> in a bowl with your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, and season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1652259118325-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1652259118325-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1652259118325-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1652259118325-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1652259118325-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry </strong>and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and cut into 1 rectangle per person</p><p>Line half a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pastry rectangle[s] </strong>to the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife (the border will puff up and form a nice crust)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1652259127577-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1652259127577-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1652259127577-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1652259127577-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1652259127577-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>soft cheese mix</strong> over the<strong> </strong>pastry within the border and top with the <strong>caramelised onion</strong> (reserve the pan), <strong>chopped spinach </strong>and <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to the other side of the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>your<strong> dried oregano</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in the oven for 25-30 min or until the pastry is cooked through and puffed up, and the potatoes are golden – this is your <strong>spinach tart </strong>and <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1652259133628-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1652259133628-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1652259133628-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1652259133628-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1652259133628-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>cherry tomatoes </strong>with your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the tomatoes have started to blister – these are your <strong>balsamic tomatoes</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of salt in a large bowl – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1652259148654-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1652259148654-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1652259148654-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1652259148654-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1652259148654-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (skin-side down) and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>,<strong> </strong>put the tray in the oven and cook for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Remove the base of your<strong> lettuce</strong>, wash under <strong>cold running water</strong> and cut away the core, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the<strong> lettuce leaves</strong> from the stem until you are left with a pile of leaves</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1652259218301-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1652259218301-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1652259218301-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1652259218301-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1652259218301-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tart is done, add the <strong>lettuce</strong> to the<strong> </strong>dressing<strong> </strong>and give it a good mix up</p><p>Flake the<strong> cooked salmon</strong> with a fork, discard the skin</p><p>Top the spinach tart<strong> </strong>with the<strong> cooked salmon flakes</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salmon & spinach tart</strong> with the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong>, <strong>dressed</strong> <strong>lettuce</strong> and <strong>balsamic tomatoes</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
